    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Collation: Paper, 96; 1-4&#xB2;&#x2070; 5&#xB2;&#x2070;&#x207B;&#x2074;(-17, -18, -19, -20); modern foliation in pencil, [1-96], lower right recto; four leaves canceled at the end of the volume.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Watermark:  Eight-pointed star above three hills (similar to the center of Briquet Monts 11933), enclosed in an oval framed with curlicues, with the letters AC below.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Script: Written in cursive script by one hand for entries for 1710-1713, with additions by another hand for 1714 (f. 34r, 66r) and multiple hands for entries from 1768 to 1772 (for example, f. 2r, 16r, 48r, 76r, 88r); title page in humanist script (f. 1r).</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Binding:  Contemporary (18th-century) parchment over pasteboard; two pairs of leather ties at foredge; spine title in ink:  Nomina et cognomina sponte comparentium, inquisitorum ac punitorum a Sancto Tribunali ab anno 1711.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Origin: Written in Siena between 1711 and 1714, with a few additions between 1768 (for example, f. 2r, 12r, 16r) and 1772 (f. 48r, 88r).</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1="0" ind2=" " tag="505">
  <marc:subfield code="a">1. f.2r: A -- 2. f.12r: B -- 3. f. 16r: C -- 4. f.20r: D -- 5. f.34r: F -- 6. f.48r: G -- 7. f.62r: I -- 8. f.66r: L -- 9. f.68r: M -- 10. f.71r: N -- 11. f.76r: P -- 12. f.88r: R -- 13. f.90r: S -- 14. f.93r: T -- 15. f.96r: U/V.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
  <marc:subfield code="a">List of approximately 130 individuals (mostly men and very few women, for example, f. 68r, 88r) questioned or punished by the Sienese Inquistion between 1711 and 1714, and between 1768 and 1772.  The brief entries of name and trial date, with occasional references to charges such as heresy or blasphemy, are arranged first alphabetically and then chronologically.  Blank pages separate the letter sections.  According to the title page (f. 1r), the list was commissioned by Iohannes Baptista Magni a Verruchio (Giovan Battista Magni da Verruchio), Inquisitor in Siena, and his seal of paper and white wax appears below the title.  The initial effort continued from 1711 to 1714.  In 1768, later hands began to add entries again until 1772.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
